 sheffield also defined the conformal loop ensembles which serve as scaling limits of the collection of all interfaces in various statistical physics models in joint work with wendelin werner he described the conformal loop ensembles as the outer boundaries of clusters of brownian loops in addition to these contributions sheffield has also proved results regarding internal diffusion limited aggregation dimers game theory partial differential equations and lipschitz extension theory education and careeredit sheffield graduated from harvard university in  with an ab and am in mathematics in  he received his phd in mathematics from stanford university before becoming a professor at mit sheffield held postdoctoral positions at microsoft research the university of california at berkeley and the institute for advanced study he was also an associate professor at new york university awardsedit scott sheffield received the loève prize the presidential early career award for scientists and engineers the sloan research fellowship and the rollo davidson prize he was also an invited speaker at the  meeting of the international congress of mathematicians in  he received the clay research award jointly with jason miller referencesedit  httpmathmitedupeopleprofilephppid mit retrieved   conformal weldings of random surfaces sle and the quantum gravity zipper scott sheffield  httparxivorgabs  contour lines of the twodimensional discrete gaussian free field oded schramm and scott sheffield  httparxivorgabsmath  a contour line of the continuum gaussian free field oded schramm and scott sheffield  httparxivorgabs  imaginary geometry i interacting sles jason miller and scott sheffield  httparxivorgabs  liouville quantum gravity and kpz bertrand duplantier and scott sheffield  httparxivorgabs  exploration trees and conformal loop ensembles scott sheffield  httparxivorgabsmath  conformal loop ensembles the markovian characterization and loop soup construction scott sheffield and wendelin w